In this program, we have discussed inheritence also called as Is-A relationship. A child class "Is-A" specialized type of its parent class.
Once class can access the properties of another class by this relationship. 
The keyword "extends" is used to inherit the properties of a class.
The object creation of the child class is enough to access the parent class properties.
It is of 5 types. i) single-level ii) multi-level iii) hierarchical iv) multiple inheritance v) Hybrif
Multiple inheritance is not supported in java. Hybrid inheritance is supported to some extent (the one with multiple inheritance is not supported).
